ps://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-01-19T10:26:10Z", "updated_at": "2020-01-20T05:51:08Z", "closed_at": "2020-01-20T05:51:08Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In quite a few places we are using `shlex.quote` for this. However, in many (if not all cases), its output is invalid on Windows. I have no good intuitive of quoting on windows, but something like:\r\n\r\n`'filename.txt'`\r\n\r\n(as produced by `shlex.quote`) is always wrong, because the single-quotes are considered part of the filename on windows.\r\n\r\nWe should establish a common cross-platform quoting helper and use that one uniformly.\r\n\r\nA draft implementation is in 94211e3 \r\n\r\nPointers:\r\n\r\n- https://pypi.org/project/mslex/\r\n- https://secure.phabricator.com/T13209\r\n- http://www.windowsinspired.com/understanding-the-command-line-string-and-arguments-received-by-a-windows-program/", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"u